# MIB-Studio Project Rules

## Critical Implementation Paths
- The core image processing must remain independent of UI framework
- OpenCV Mat objects need conversion to Qt-compatible formats (QImage) for display
- All UI updates must be thread-safe and non-blocking
- Performance metrics should be collected with minimal overhead

## Project Preferences
- Use Qt6 rather than Qt5
- Prefer Qt's signals/slots for communication between components
- Use QtCharts for all metric visualizations
- Maintain CMake/vcpkg for dependency management
- Follow Qt naming conventions for new Qt-specific code

## Code Style
- Use camelCase for methods and variables
- Use PascalCase for class names
- Use snake_case for file names
- Document all public interfaces using doxygen-style comments
- Group related functionality into namespaces

## File Organization
- Qt UI files (.ui) should be in a dedicated ui/ directory
- Qt resource files (.qrc) should be in a resources/ directory
- Separate processing logic from UI code where possible
- Use include guards with project prefix (e.g., MIB_STUDIO_HEADER_H)

## Build Process
- Always update vcpkg before adding new dependencies
- Use CMake's find_package for detecting Qt components
- Configure Qt's MOC, UIC, and RCC in CMakeLists.txt
- Add separate build targets for UI-related components

## Testing Strategy
- UI changes should not break existing image processing logic
- Performance benchmarks must be run before and after Qt integration
- Test on multiple platforms if possible (Windows priority)
- Test with various camera resolutions and frame rates 